    "Match key: (raw.status, raw.changed, raw.created). A null in 'when' means the dimension does not discriminate for that row.",
    "raw.created means the target file did not exist when the audit ran. distributeRepo results do not carry existence, so M1's refresh engine computes it from its own pre-reconcile existence probe and stamps it into RepoRefreshReport raw blocks.",
    "operation.currentState null means scenario-dependent: M1 computes it from the concrete finding (e.g. a skipped item may be a missing or a present file); the action mapping stays exactly-one regardless.",
    "options lists the closed resolution vocabulary a DecisionDoc item with this state offers; an empty list means there is no decision to make (the item is informational)."
  ],
